# Panel

## Introduction

The Panel component shows white text against a turquoise background. This is used for transactions end pages and Bank Holidays.


[Preview the Panel component](https://govuk-frontend-review.herokuapp.com/components/panel/preview).

Read guidance on when to use the Panel component in your service in the [GOV.UK Design System]([Insert link to component page in the Design System]).

## Dependencies

You must be running [npm version 5 or above](http://blog.npmjs.org/post/161081169345/v500)  to use the Panel component.

The Panel component depends on @govuk-frontend/globals, which will automatically be installed with the package.


## Installation

Install the Panel component by running the command:

    [npm install code]

## Configuration

To use the Panel component you need to setup your build tool to find the package in the node_modules.

When compiling the Sass files you’ll need to define includePaths to reference the node_modules directory.

Below is a sample configuration using Gulp js:

    .pipe(sass({ includePaths: 'node_modules/' }))

### Static asset path configuration

To show the Panel image you need to configure your app. Use the sample configuration in Express js to do this:

    app.use('/public', express.static(path.join(__dirname, '/node_modules/@govuk-frontend/icons')))

